#. type: Plain text
#: original_texis/display.texi:4290
msgid "@var{fringe} is either the symbol @code{left-fringe} or @code{right-fringe}.  @var{bitmap} is a symbol identifying the bitmap to display.  The optional @var{face} names a face whose foreground and background colors are to be used to display the bitmap, using the attributes of the @code{fringe} face for colors that @var{face} didn't specify.  If @var{face} is omitted, that means to use the attributes of the @code{default} face for the colors which the @code{fringe} face didn't specify.  For predictable results that don't depend on the attributes of the @code{default} and @code{fringe} faces, we recommend you never omit @var{face}, but always provide a specific face.  In particular, if you want the bitmap to be always displayed in the @code{fringe} face, use @code{fringe} as @var{face}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: original_texis/display.texi:4293
